WEBVTT

1
00:02:15.510 --> 00:02:17.012
Please! Please.

2
00:02:17.094 --> 00:02:19.348
Can you turn off the light?
Just for a few hours--

3
00:03:02.682 --> 00:03:05.394
And security is ramping up in Paris
as the city prepares

4
00:03:05.477 --> 00:03:08.312
for the opening ceremony
of the Summer Olympic Games.

5
00:03:08.396 --> 00:03:11.733
Organizers are promising a dazzling
spectacle with plenty of surprises.

6
00:03:11.817 --> 00:03:14.068
and later in the hour.
we're gonna take you behind the scenes

7
00:03:14.151 --> 00:03:15.820
and show you
how some of that magic is made.

8
00:03:15.903 --> 00:03:20.741
And finally. it's day 28 of
Bradley Jackson's detainment in Belarus.

9
00:03:20.825 --> 00:03:22.870
We hope and pray that she will come home--

10
00:03:48.770 --> 00:03:50.438
I understand. I understand.

11
00:03:51.147 --> 00:03:56.485
But it has been a month. and every day
we keep having the exact same conversation

12
00:03:56.569 --> 00:03:58.906
while people are forgetting
what's happening to her.

13
00:03:59.615 --> 00:04:02.074
Yes. No. I understand. Thank you.

14
00:04:04.328 --> 00:04:07.080
Well. they still won't designate
Bradley as unlawfully detained.

15
00:04:07.163 --> 00:04:09.373
Not until they have more information.

16
00:04:09.457 --> 00:04:13.586
So. we can just add that to the list
of fucked-up shit we cannot fix.

17
00:04:14.587 --> 00:04:16.379
Did you hear anything that I just said?

18
00:04:16.923 --> 00:04:19.300
What? Yes. Come here.
You have to see this.

19
00:04:20.552 --> 00:04:22.512
- Come here. Look. Look. look. look.
- What's that?

20
00:04:22.596 --> 00:04:24.348
Okay. This is the EPA report
on Wolf River.

21
00:04:24.430 --> 00:04:26.057
the one from 2019. right?

22
00:04:26.141 --> 00:04:30.896
This is the internal Martel emissions doc
that Bradley sent over.

23
00:04:33.814 --> 00:04:35.233
They're nowhere close.

24
00:04:35.317 --> 00:04:37.944
- The EPA numbers are way lower.
- It's way lower.

25
00:04:38.028 --> 00:04:40.279
And. I mean. I don't wanna sound crazy.

26
00:04:40.363 --> 00:04:42.533
but what if somebody falsified
the EPA report?

27
00:04:42.615 --> 00:04:44.742
And maybe…
maybe Martel paid them to do it.

28
00:04:44.826 --> 00:04:47.620
I don't know. That's sounding
a little bit like a Bro conspiracy theory.

29
00:04:47.704 --> 00:04:48.997
What. you mean the future Senator Hartman?

30
00:04:49.081 --> 00:04:50.540
- Don't say that.
- Okay. look.

31
00:04:50.624 --> 00:04:52.834
- Just "what if" for a second. okay?
- Okay. okay.

32
00:04:53.418 --> 00:04:56.004
Bradley's source works at Martel. okay.
She clearly was onto something

33
00:04:56.088 --> 00:04:57.338
they didn't want her to know about.

34
00:04:57.422 --> 00:05:02.386
If we can somehow prove that there was
a cover-up involving the EPA.

35
00:05:03.262 --> 00:05:04.262
that's front-page news.

36
00:05:04.346 --> 00:05:06.139
And then people start talking
about Bradley again.

37
00:05:06.223 --> 00:05:08.307
That's it. that's it.
So now we just need to find somebody

38
00:05:08.391 --> 00:05:10.060
who knows more about these numbers.

39
00:05:10.143 --> 00:05:11.185
Wait. Bradley.

40
00:05:11.269 --> 00:05:14.146
Didn't she say something
about Cory and the EPA report?

41
00:05:14.689 --> 00:05:16.733
Remember? And that's
why he didn't run the story?

42
00:05:17.317 --> 00:05:20.028
Maybe Cory lied.
Maybe he's just covering his ass.

43
00:05:20.862 --> 00:05:22.029
Jesus. Alex.

44
00:05:22.990 --> 00:05:26.326
This means Bradley was right.
About all of it.

45
00:05:43.468 --> 00:05:45.095
You are having trouble sleeping?

46
00:05:45.762 --> 00:05:46.846
Yes.

47
00:05:47.680 --> 00:05:49.098
The light never turns off.

48
00:05:50.350 --> 00:05:51.350
Please.

49
00:05:51.435 --> 00:05:53.812
Who were you meeting in Minsk?

50
00:05:53.896 --> 00:05:56.023
I ca… I can't.

51
00:05:56.105 --> 00:05:57.774
I need a name.

52
00:05:59.067 --> 00:06:01.778
Please. this person is not a dissident. I…

53
00:06:02.862 --> 00:06:04.156
I'm not a spy.

54
00:06:05.115 --> 00:06:06.365
I'm not a spy.

55
00:06:31.057 --> 00:06:33.268
- Shit.
- That's a cut!

56
00:06:35.312 --> 00:06:38.189
Goddamn it. Eric?
How long is it gonna take to fix this?

57
00:06:38.273 --> 00:06:39.441
Give us a minute.

58
00:06:40.442 --> 00:06:41.944
It's like The Matrix. Wow.

59
00:06:42.026 --> 00:06:44.571
Yeah. And I'm dodging
twice as many bullets.

60
00:06:44.654 --> 00:06:45.988
Well. at least you're back up and running.

61
00:06:46.072 --> 00:06:48.283
How are things going with
the fancy new star?

62
00:06:48.367 --> 00:06:50.576
Hey. how about you just ask me
what you came here to ask me.

63
00:06:50.661 --> 00:06:53.704
- 'cause I'm a little busy right now.
- Not in the mood for foreplay. huh?

64
00:06:53.788 --> 00:06:56.959
Well. life is short and I love you.
but I'm not in love with you.

65
00:06:57.042 --> 00:06:58.043
Okay.

66
00:06:58.125 --> 00:06:59.836
So I have been sifting
through the information

67
00:06:59.920 --> 00:07:02.047
that Bradley sent over
before she was detained.

68
00:07:02.129 --> 00:07:04.048
It's paperwork from Martel Chemical.

69
00:07:04.132 --> 00:07:07.927
Soil reports. groundwater tests.
and there's something weird.

70
00:07:08.011 --> 00:07:12.348
The internal numbers of Martel don't match
the EPA report on Wolf River.

71
00:07:13.057 --> 00:07:14.350
You know anything about this?

72
00:07:15.519 --> 00:07:17.396
No. I don't.

73
00:07:18.521 --> 00:07:20.481
Really? You're totally in the dark?

74
00:07:20.565 --> 00:07:22.317
As I explained to Bradley.

75
00:07:23.192 --> 00:07:28.072
legal told me to move on
from the story in 2019. so I did.

76
00:07:28.156 --> 00:07:31.242
I turned that page in my life.
and I'm not trying to go back.

77
00:07:31.326 --> 00:07:32.451
- Okay. I get it--
- All right.

78
00:07:32.536 --> 00:07:36.290
But even if it means
we could bring Bradley back home?

79
00:07:36.372 --> 00:07:38.959
The only people
that can help Bradley right now

80
00:07:39.042 --> 00:07:40.711
are the fine folks
at the State Department.

81
00:07:40.793 --> 00:07:43.088
I agree. And if we break Bradley's story.

82
00:07:43.172 --> 00:07:45.382
then it'll put pressure on them
to get on it. right?

83
00:07:45.465 --> 00:07:47.466
Yeah. well. that's certainly a theory.

84
00:07:49.218 --> 00:07:50.637
Well… Come on. man.

85
00:07:50.721 --> 00:07:53.473
Like. I don't really know what's going on
between Bradley and the feds.

86
00:07:53.557 --> 00:07:56.851
but they're clearly not bending over
backwards to help her right now.

87
00:07:56.935 --> 00:08:00.480
Well. yeah. I mean. karma sucks.
doesn't it. Chip?

88
00:08:01.814 --> 00:08:02.899
What is wrong with you?

89
00:08:03.483 --> 00:08:04.483
Come again?

90
00:08:05.276 --> 00:08:06.653
She's in a fucking gulag. man.

91
00:08:06.737 --> 00:08:08.654
I understand you're mad at her
or something. but like--

92
00:08:08.738 --> 00:08:09.740
Mad?

93
00:08:09.822 --> 00:08:12.992
As I'm sure you know.
she strip-mined my phone.

94
00:08:13.076 --> 00:08:17.372
and. I don't know. my fucking soul
on all things Wolf River.

95
00:08:17.456 --> 00:08:20.417
Perfect timing. by the way. It really
set me up for the last couple of weeks.

96
00:08:20.500 --> 00:08:23.545
I don't know if you've ever had
the honor of picking out an urn

97
00:08:23.629 --> 00:08:25.547
for the pile of dust
formerly called your mother.

98
00:08:25.630 --> 00:08:28.550
There's so many choices.
They got rosewood. they got ceramic.

99
00:08:28.634 --> 00:08:30.552
they got biodegradable. they got engraved.

100
00:08:30.636 --> 00:08:33.846
It is fantastic how we've managed
to incorporate death

101
00:08:33.931 --> 00:08:36.432
into the consumer economy.
While we're on the subject.

102
00:08:36.517 --> 00:08:38.433
quick question.
what do you think is worse?

103
00:08:39.144 --> 00:08:42.437
Pretending to love someone
so you can fuck 'em over.

104
00:08:42.523 --> 00:08:45.234
or killing yourself in front of them?

105
00:08:46.360 --> 00:08:48.236
It's… you know… I just…

106
00:08:51.280 --> 00:08:52.323
Okay. I'm gonna go.

107
00:08:52.407 --> 00:08:54.576
Well. that's the best idea
you had all day.

108
00:08:55.369 --> 00:08:57.453
Copy of the EPA report on Wolf River.

109
00:08:57.538 --> 00:08:58.746
Maybe it'll jog your memory.

110
00:09:07.047 --> 00:09:08.673
And for what it's worth. man.

111
00:09:09.383 --> 00:09:12.510
Bradley was genuinely torn up
about what happened between you two.

112
00:09:14.221 --> 00:09:15.972
I think it really got to her.

113
00:09:17.557 --> 00:09:18.683
I'm sorry for your loss.

114
00:09:56.596 --> 00:09:58.807
- You don't look well.
- No.

115
00:10:00.267 --> 00:10:01.934
Are you ready to sleep?

116
00:10:02.811 --> 00:10:03.979
Yes.

117
00:10:10.193 --> 00:10:12.653
The name. then sleep.

118
00:10:15.240 --> 00:10:17.576
We just want to talk to them.

119
00:10:18.284 --> 00:10:19.369
That's all.

120
00:11:18.928 --> 00:11:20.346
Why did you come back?

121
00:11:22.850 --> 00:11:24.100
For you. obviously.

122
00:11:25.309 --> 00:11:27.729
Well. yeah. I get that.
I'm totally irresistible.

123
00:11:29.438 --> 00:11:30.941
Why did I come back?

124
00:11:32.234 --> 00:11:33.442
I don't know.

125
00:11:34.318 --> 00:11:35.736
I mean. if I'm being honest.

126
00:11:36.363 --> 00:11:38.532
it was a little bit boring
teaching journalism.

127
00:11:40.993 --> 00:11:44.370
Also. I figured if nobody was gonna
punish me for what I did.

128
00:11:45.873 --> 00:11:47.331
guess I could punish myself.

129
00:11:52.336 --> 00:11:54.798
Maybe it's time to stop being punished.

130
00:11:55.631 --> 00:11:57.301
Maybe there's been enough of that.

131
00:12:02.431 --> 00:12:04.265
You know what I keep thinking about?

132
00:12:07.811 --> 00:12:09.395
The night you told me you loved me.

133
00:12:12.441 --> 00:12:15.193
Even when your brother was missing
and you thought he might be dead?

134
00:12:15.277 --> 00:12:17.236
Well. see.
that's what's so great about you.

135
00:12:17.321 --> 00:12:19.697
is you have impeccable sense of timing.

136
00:12:20.448 --> 00:12:22.743
Well. it's only been four years.

137
00:12:22.826 --> 00:12:25.203
You feel like you're ready
to get back to me on that?

138
00:12:28.539 --> 00:12:30.375
You scared the shit out of me that night.

139
00:12:33.003 --> 00:12:35.297
Then how did we end up here?

140
00:12:39.342 --> 00:12:41.720
Maybe I just wanted to figure out
what I was so scared of.

141
00:12:48.018 --> 00:12:49.186
Any answers?

142
00:12:50.520 --> 00:12:51.562
I don't know.

143
00:12:53.273 --> 00:12:54.399
It's like.

144
00:12:56.192 --> 00:12:57.443
there's you.

145
00:12:58.861 --> 00:13:00.530
and then there's everybody else.

146
00:13:03.158 --> 00:13:04.534
But there's you.

147
00:13:07.955 --> 00:13:09.248
And you're always with me.

148
00:13:11.166 --> 00:13:12.875
Even when I don't want you to be.

149
00:13:14.961 --> 00:13:16.087
You got in.

150
00:13:18.756 --> 00:13:20.299
I don't know how you did it.

151
00:13:21.884 --> 00:13:23.052
But you did.

152
00:13:33.730 --> 00:13:35.023
So…

153
00:13:38.902 --> 00:13:40.278
are we gonna try this?

154
00:13:44.866 --> 00:13:46.784
I'm gonna fuck it up a little.

155
00:13:46.869 --> 00:13:47.870
Me too.

156
00:13:50.956 --> 00:13:53.000
Well. as long as it's not just me.

157
00:13:55.418 --> 00:13:59.881
I will do my very best to disappoint you.

158
00:14:01.758 --> 00:14:02.801
Good.

159
00:14:28.118 --> 00:14:29.202
Hey.

160
00:14:29.286 --> 00:14:31.163
- Hey.
- You're here late.

161
00:14:31.746 --> 00:14:34.124
You know me.
The Games are around the corner. So…

162
00:14:34.790 --> 00:14:38.669
Actually. I was looking for Layla.
but maybe you can help me?

163
00:14:39.754 --> 00:14:42.090
After the whole Stella O24…

164
00:14:42.173 --> 00:14:43.299
Nuclear meltdown?

165
00:14:43.383 --> 00:14:46.385
Well. I was gonna say. "situation."

166
00:14:46.470 --> 00:14:48.179
- but yeah. sure.
- Okay.

167
00:14:48.764 --> 00:14:51.225
We've been triple-checking
the few AI elements

168
00:14:51.307 --> 00:14:52.893
that we're gonna roll out in Paris.

169
00:14:52.975 --> 00:14:56.812
In case Yanko's avatar starts talking
about how his radicalized ex-girlfriend

170
00:14:56.897 --> 00:14:58.649
got dragged out of the building
by the FBI?

171
00:14:58.731 --> 00:15:00.817
It's… It's funny you should mention that.

172
00:15:00.900 --> 00:15:05.154
So. IT flagged something in their report.

173
00:15:05.239 --> 00:15:09.993
It looks like there was some unauthorized
access of the Alex language model

174
00:15:10.076 --> 00:15:11.620
from a TMS computer.

175
00:15:11.702 --> 00:15:15.999
This happened a couple of months ago.
Before you left. In May.

176
00:15:16.833 --> 00:15:19.378
Do you mind taking a look at it for me?
I'm kinda buried.

177
00:15:19.461 --> 00:15:21.212
TMS is not my problem anymore.

178
00:15:21.296 --> 00:15:24.674
Well. it happened on your watch. so…

179
00:15:25.967 --> 00:15:27.594
I'd really appreciate it.

180
00:15:30.138 --> 00:15:31.431
Yeah. Sure.

181
00:15:31.514 --> 00:15:32.850
Thank you.

182
00:15:33.558 --> 00:15:34.643
You're welcome.

183
00:17:03.023 --> 00:17:06.276
Do you remember anyone working
on AI projects for TMS back in May?

184
00:17:06.358 --> 00:17:09.319
Somebody who would have had access
to Alex's avatar?

185
00:17:09.819 --> 00:17:11.448
Not really. and why would anyone do that?

186
00:17:11.530 --> 00:17:13.866
Yeah. I thought
all the AI stuff was Ben's team?

187
00:17:13.951 --> 00:17:16.286
TMS is very hands-off on that.

188
00:17:16.368 --> 00:17:19.373
- Right? Yeah.
- Right. Yeah. Thanks.

189
00:18:51.923 --> 00:18:53.049
Cory?

190
00:19:03.309 --> 00:19:04.353
What is it?

191
00:19:08.315 --> 00:19:09.398
What's wrong?

192
00:19:23.829 --> 00:19:26.250
Did you have something to do
with Bradley getting taken?

193
00:19:28.876 --> 00:19:31.880
- Cory…
- Hey. just tell me.

194
00:19:31.963 --> 00:19:33.632
Of course not.

195
00:19:35.133 --> 00:19:36.509
Why would you think that?

196
00:19:36.593 --> 00:19:39.387
Well. your family must have
a financial interest in Martel

197
00:19:39.471 --> 00:19:42.598
since you paid Fred to bury the story.

198
00:19:42.682 --> 00:19:44.393
I thought we'd put this behind us.

199
00:19:44.476 --> 00:19:46.519
Yeah. we did. but Bradley brought it back.

200
00:19:49.021 --> 00:19:50.898
She was getting close.

201
00:19:52.651 --> 00:19:54.236
She was getting close to something.

202
00:19:55.028 --> 00:19:57.655
and now not even the Red Cross
can get in to see her.

203
00:20:00.200 --> 00:20:03.036
And you think
I had something to do with that?

204
00:20:03.537 --> 00:20:05.873
I don't know what to think.

205
00:20:12.378 --> 00:20:13.797
No one knew she was going.

206
00:20:15.590 --> 00:20:18.426
Ask Alex. Ask anyone.

207
00:20:18.509 --> 00:20:22.431
I think your family can help get her out.
And I think I can help your family.

208
00:20:23.807 --> 00:20:29.020
Chip is looking into all of this.
and he's circling around the EPA report.

209
00:20:29.104 --> 00:20:31.397
But he doesn't know
that I have the real one.

210
00:20:32.982 --> 00:20:36.737
The one that proves that Martel is liable

211
00:20:36.819 --> 00:20:39.239
for all the things they did
to those people.

212
00:20:41.700 --> 00:20:46.246
And once Bradley is back.
you and your family can have the report.

213
00:20:49.708 --> 00:20:51.167
An insurance policy.

214
00:20:51.919 --> 00:20:53.711
Do whatever the fuck you want with it.

215
00:20:55.506 --> 00:20:58.258
My family. they can't wave a magic wand.

216
00:20:58.342 --> 00:21:00.009
They can do something.

217
00:21:05.223 --> 00:21:06.224
Maybe.

218
00:21:10.854 --> 00:21:11.980
I'll call them.

219
00:21:13.773 --> 00:21:14.775
For you.

220
00:21:20.239 --> 00:21:21.280
Cory…

221
00:21:27.703 --> 00:21:29.288
I know you feel alone.

222
00:21:30.414 --> 00:21:31.541
But I'm here.

223
00:21:32.667 --> 00:21:33.794
I'm with you.

224
00:21:40.675 --> 00:21:41.926
Come back to bed.

225
00:21:43.636 --> 00:21:44.680
All right?

226
00:21:57.233 --> 00:21:58.234
Hello?

227
00:22:05.616 --> 00:22:06.868
Bart.

228
00:22:06.951 --> 00:22:08.202
What are you doing here?

229
00:22:12.415 --> 00:22:13.834
Deepfake of Alex?

230
00:22:15.794 --> 00:22:19.047
You were there when the Iranians defected.
producing the segment.

231
00:22:20.757 --> 00:22:23.134
Then you accessed the AI software.

232
00:22:24.303 --> 00:22:25.304
Why?

233
00:22:27.890 --> 00:22:29.432
Who told you to do that?

234
00:22:32.477 --> 00:22:36.022
Tell me what you know
and I'll keep your name out of it.

235
00:22:49.744 --> 00:22:50.746
Mia…

236
00:23:07.512 --> 00:23:09.347
Ms… Ms. Levy?

237
00:23:11.432 --> 00:23:14.102
You lied to me. You fucking lied.

238
00:23:14.685 --> 00:23:17.021
The Iranians did not create that deepfake.

239
00:23:17.105 --> 00:23:18.190
You did.

240
00:23:18.272 --> 00:23:21.777
Do you know how much that fucked me up?

241
00:23:22.402 --> 00:23:25.154
You stole my voice. You used me.

242
00:23:25.239 --> 00:23:26.490
I don't even know
what you're talking about.

243
00:23:26.573 --> 00:23:30.243
You were going to use that video
to get me fired.

244
00:23:30.326 --> 00:23:31.912
and the only reason you didn't

245
00:23:31.994 --> 00:23:35.540
is because things got complicated
with Zeke and those protesters.

246
00:23:36.541 --> 00:23:37.792
My God. I'm starting to question

247
00:23:37.875 --> 00:23:40.921
every single thing you have done
since you got here.

248
00:23:41.003 --> 00:23:44.340
Preach sisterhood
and then you edge all of us out.

249
00:23:44.967 --> 00:23:47.051
Laura. me. Stella…

250
00:23:48.261 --> 00:23:50.305
So now you're blaming me
for her fuck-up too.

251
00:23:50.931 --> 00:23:53.517
I expect your resignation
by the end of today.

252
00:23:54.852 --> 00:23:57.938
Otherwise. I go to the board
and The New York Times.

253
00:24:00.816 --> 00:24:01.942
I'm sorry.

254
00:24:03.402 --> 00:24:06.113
I'm not resigning. You are.

255
00:24:07.990 --> 00:24:09.782
And why would I do that?

256
00:24:09.866 --> 00:24:12.869
Do you know how many laws you broke
when you went to the opera?

257
00:24:14.037 --> 00:24:17.915
You did business with a Russian oligarch
sanctioned by the US government.

258
00:24:18.000 --> 00:24:20.836
The FCC could shut us down
for a stunt like that.

259
00:24:20.919 --> 00:24:22.962
As an executive at this company.

260
00:24:23.713 --> 00:24:27.259
you acted against the well-being
of UBN and its shareholders.

261
00:24:29.260 --> 00:24:31.180
You have 24 hours to step down.

262
00:25:01.084 --> 00:25:02.336
She knows.

263
00:25:02.419 --> 00:25:06.632
Ivanov. the trade we were trying to make.
everything.

264
00:25:06.714 --> 00:25:09.675
I should have never reached out to him.
I knew this could blow back on us.

265
00:25:09.759 --> 00:25:11.178
How the fuck did she find out?

266
00:25:11.260 --> 00:25:12.887
I don't know. I don't know.

267
00:25:12.971 --> 00:25:17.017
She just told me that I have 24 hours
to resign or she's gonna call the feds.

268
00:25:18.059 --> 00:25:19.310
Alex. that cannot happen.

269
00:25:19.810 --> 00:25:22.855
- Nobody can find out about this.
- I know that. I know.

270
00:25:23.648 --> 00:25:24.942
Bradley. What about Bradley?

271
00:25:25.901 --> 00:25:28.403
State Department already
dragging its feet.

272
00:25:29.112 --> 00:25:33.825
Celine. she knew something like this
would completely compromise her case.

273
00:25:33.909 --> 00:25:35.451
Bradley fucking Jackson.

274
00:25:36.118 --> 00:25:38.579
My God. Stuck in a fucking gulag
in Eastern Europe

275
00:25:38.663 --> 00:25:40.332
and she's still a human wrecking ball.

276
00:25:40.414 --> 00:25:43.585
I just can't… can't believe
this 22 years. this is how it ends.

277
00:25:44.169 --> 00:25:46.171
I worked so fucking hard for that place.

278
00:25:46.255 --> 00:25:48.382
Hey. hey. hey. hey. Listen to me.

279
00:25:49.924 --> 00:25:51.134
You stopped me.

280
00:25:52.134 --> 00:25:54.054
All right. I'm pretty sure
you can shut her down.

281
00:25:54.136 --> 00:25:56.431
Now. if she knows
about some off-book trade.

282
00:25:56.515 --> 00:25:59.893
then she's doing some backroom deals
of her own. which makes her vulnerable.

283
00:25:59.977 --> 00:26:01.936
- You're right.
- So dig.

284
00:26:02.019 --> 00:26:05.190
Find out where the bodies are buried.
Who knows her secrets?

285
00:26:15.409 --> 00:26:16.576
- Hi.
- Hi.

286
00:26:16.660 --> 00:26:19.453
So sorry to drop in like this.
I know you have so much going on.

287
00:26:19.538 --> 00:26:22.374
- It's actually not a good time.
- I'm sorry. But I can't wait. honestly.

288
00:26:22.457 --> 00:26:26.502
She wants me out.
Celine is forcing me out.

289
00:26:26.586 --> 00:26:29.463
I'm supposed to… to resign.
I'm supposed to step aside

290
00:26:29.548 --> 00:26:31.924
- like it's my fucking idea…
- Hey. can we talk about this tomorrow?

291
00:26:32.009 --> 00:26:33.259
…and I'm not gonna fucking do that.

292
00:26:33.343 --> 00:26:35.304
I know this has everything
to do with Bradley.

293
00:26:35.386 --> 00:26:37.931
I can't prove it. but I know it.

294
00:26:38.015 --> 00:26:42.728
And Cory. I know that you know her well.
so just give me some… some dirt on her.

295
00:26:42.810 --> 00:26:44.938
Come on. You traffic in this shit.

296
00:26:45.480 --> 00:26:47.273
I don't care what it is. Insider trading.

297
00:26:47.356 --> 00:26:49.483
Tax evasion. I don't care.

298
00:26:49.567 --> 00:26:51.278
I just need something.

299
00:26:51.361 --> 00:26:52.863
Sorry I'm late.

300
00:26:57.951 --> 00:26:58.951
I had…

301
00:27:12.257 --> 00:27:14.092
Okay. Of course.

302
00:27:16.511 --> 00:27:17.512
I mean. just…

303
00:27:20.641 --> 00:27:21.933
Why wouldn't you?

304
00:27:36.030 --> 00:27:41.662
Alex. you have been the heart and soul of
this network now for so long.

305
00:27:41.744 --> 00:27:44.163
How does it feel to be saying goodbye?

306
00:27:44.248 --> 00:27:47.334
It honestly… bittersweet.

307
00:27:47.416 --> 00:27:52.130
You know. this place has been my… my home.
You guys are my family.

308
00:27:52.213 --> 00:27:55.968
Heck. I know. Well. we feel the same way.
We just… I mean. this is so sudden.

309
00:27:56.050 --> 00:27:58.177
Honestly. I just can't
quite believe it's happening at all.

310
00:27:58.261 --> 00:28:01.807
Yeah. I know. Well. it's…
it's something that I've been. you know.

311
00:28:01.890 --> 00:28:04.977
I've been thinking about for a while. so…

312
00:28:05.602 --> 00:28:06.854
Well. we're gonna miss you in Paris.

313
00:28:06.936 --> 00:28:09.105
That's for sure. right?

314
00:28:09.189 --> 00:28:14.152
Can you talk about your decision?
What brought you to this moment?

315
00:28:15.112 --> 00:28:17.614
Well. two years ago.

316
00:28:17.698 --> 00:28:21.785
I think we felt the company
needed to change.

317
00:28:21.868 --> 00:28:26.914
so I stayed through the merger
to help make UBN a place

318
00:28:26.999 --> 00:28:29.585
that we could be proud of. where…

319
00:28:32.880 --> 00:28:36.258
there's real transparency.

320
00:28:36.340 --> 00:28:37.342
Real trust.

321
00:28:38.218 --> 00:28:39.927
And you feel we've achieved that.

322
00:28:44.016 --> 00:28:46.894
I do. Yes. I do.

323
00:28:48.228 --> 00:28:51.856
And you know my…
my best memories of this place.

324
00:28:51.940 --> 00:28:53.942
it's not ju… you know.
not just the fun times we had

325
00:28:54.026 --> 00:28:55.152
'cause we would have a lot of fun.

326
00:28:55.234 --> 00:28:59.323
but it's also the storms
that we weathered together. you know.

327
00:28:59.405 --> 00:29:02.659
And… Yeah. everybody said
that we would never make it.

328
00:29:03.743 --> 00:29:10.209
that legacy media was dead.
and real journalism doesn't matter.

329
00:29:11.710 --> 00:29:17.465
But it really does matter. right?
It matters more than ever.

330
00:29:17.548 --> 00:29:20.384
Well. you've absolutely been our…
our resident truth-teller.

331
00:29:20.469 --> 00:29:23.262
I mean. it's Unfiltered. you know.
Right there in the title of it.

332
00:29:41.949 --> 00:29:43.075
Miles.

333
00:29:44.409 --> 00:29:45.410
Celine.

334
00:29:50.540 --> 00:29:51.916
Why are you here?

335
00:29:53.085 --> 00:29:54.377
You haven't called.

336
00:29:55.336 --> 00:29:56.838
This is my home.

337
00:29:57.631 --> 00:30:00.008
- I live here.
- Well. not recently.

338
00:30:00.550 --> 00:30:01.718
I needed time to think.

339
00:30:03.470 --> 00:30:05.972
And what great revelation
did you have out there in the woods?

340
00:30:06.056 --> 00:30:08.724
That I wanted to come back.

341
00:30:09.684 --> 00:30:11.144
figure things out.

342
00:30:12.061 --> 00:30:14.981
But then. I found this.

343
00:30:18.402 --> 00:30:21.904
You were there at the studio without me.

344
00:30:24.740 --> 00:30:27.035
Please. Miles. After what you did--

345
00:30:27.118 --> 00:30:28.412
Who were you with?

346
00:30:28.494 --> 00:30:30.998
Do you understand I wasn't sure
I'd ever see you again?

347
00:30:31.080 --> 00:30:33.625
Celine. who was it?

348
00:30:45.929 --> 00:30:48.515
- Yep.
- Ms. Levy. your father is here.

349
00:30:52.227 --> 00:30:53.519
Send him up.

350
00:30:56.647 --> 00:30:58.150
Dad.

351
00:30:58.232 --> 00:31:00.318
I've just had such a long day.

352
00:31:00.402 --> 00:31:02.445
Don't worry. I won't stay long.

353
00:31:02.528 --> 00:31:06.365
I realize that
after our last brief encounter.

354
00:31:07.201 --> 00:31:09.452
I'm not the most welcome person here.

355
00:31:10.037 --> 00:31:13.039
I just don't have it in me for
another round of all of that. you know.

356
00:31:13.123 --> 00:31:16.751
No. no. no. None of that. I think
we both said all we needed to say.

357
00:31:17.419 --> 00:31:19.171
No. it was just that I…

358
00:31:20.797 --> 00:31:22.508
Well. I saw your show today.

359
00:31:25.635 --> 00:31:28.931
Quite sudden. your decision to step away.

360
00:31:29.431 --> 00:31:33.101
It's funny that all of a sudden
now you take interest in my career.

361
00:31:33.769 --> 00:31:35.269
The day that it's over.

362
00:31:40.483 --> 00:31:43.444
Is this about losing the Biden interview?

363
00:31:44.445 --> 00:31:46.073
You know. no. It's just…

364
00:31:47.490 --> 00:31:49.116
It's just… it was time.

365
00:31:49.201 --> 00:31:50.536
I saw you at work.

366
00:31:51.036 --> 00:31:55.164
You were in your element.
utterly engaged with the task at hand.

367
00:31:56.959 --> 00:31:59.920
You didn't look like someone
with one foot out of the door.

368
00:32:00.711 --> 00:32:04.799
Heck. you reminded me of me
when I was your age.

369
00:32:06.718 --> 00:32:10.430
Your performance today might have
fooled America.

370
00:32:10.513 --> 00:32:12.682
But remember. I've been about a bit.

371
00:32:12.766 --> 00:32:15.853
I know the hallmarks
of a forced confession.

372
00:32:20.898 --> 00:32:22.733
Do you want to talk to me about it?

373
00:32:25.444 --> 00:32:27.071
It's such a long story.

374
00:32:27.780 --> 00:32:32.118
Well. that's the beauty
of a public disgrace.

375
00:32:33.828 --> 00:32:36.289
Suddenly all you have is time.

376
00:32:37.249 --> 00:32:39.960
Yeah. we gotta move
the production meeting up 'cause the…

377
00:32:40.042 --> 00:32:42.171
What the… Fuck me. I'll call you back.

378
00:32:46.258 --> 00:32:48.301
- We need to talk.
- Miles. hi.

379
00:32:48.384 --> 00:32:49.385
Well. yeah.

380
00:32:50.721 --> 00:32:51.971
Come on in.

381
00:32:52.806 --> 00:32:55.933
Hey. Cory.
I should throw you out a fucking window!

382
00:32:56.018 --> 00:32:57.185
Please don't.

383
00:32:58.144 --> 00:32:59.520
What do you want with my wife?

384
00:32:59.605 --> 00:33:01.190
You know. we've got
a business arrangement.

385
00:33:02.191 --> 00:33:03.357
Is that what you're calling it?

386
00:33:03.442 --> 00:33:06.694
Your late-night coke binge
with a little fucking on the side.

387
00:33:06.778 --> 00:33:09.155
We have been
helping each other out a little bit.

388
00:33:09.239 --> 00:33:10.574
You sure as shit haven't been around.

389
00:33:10.656 --> 00:33:12.034
- How's Stella?
- Fuck you.

390
00:33:12.116 --> 00:33:14.286
You think she's on your side?
You think she's got your back?

391
00:33:14.368 --> 00:33:16.413
Like I said. we have an arrangement.

392
00:33:17.079 --> 00:33:19.208
You have no idea. do you?
You can't see it.

393
00:33:19.290 --> 00:33:21.250
You're the fall guy. Cory.

394
00:33:21.792 --> 00:33:24.337
You always have been
ever since she made you Head of News.

395
00:33:24.421 --> 00:33:26.923
Buddy. you're talking about Wolf River?
I already know about this.

396
00:33:27.007 --> 00:33:28.842
And I should've known that
you knew about it too.

397
00:33:28.925 --> 00:33:30.801
You have no idea what you were part of.

398
00:33:30.885 --> 00:33:33.931
I think I do. I read the real EPA report.

399
00:33:34.013 --> 00:33:36.474
Parting gift from my mother. Remember her?

400
00:33:36.557 --> 00:33:38.519
She figured out that
Celine was gonna bury it.

401
00:33:38.602 --> 00:33:40.479
so she left me a copy.

402
00:33:40.561 --> 00:33:42.897
My own little get-out-of-jail-free card.

403
00:33:42.980 --> 00:33:46.234
You think…
You think Martha was a whistleblower?

404
00:33:47.568 --> 00:33:48.903
Cory.

405
00:33:48.987 --> 00:33:50.739
No. no. She was part of it.

406
00:33:51.615 --> 00:33:53.241
She brokered the deal with Celine.

407
00:33:53.325 --> 00:33:55.201
Miles. you don't know
what the fuck you're talking about.

408
00:33:55.285 --> 00:33:59.248
No. no. Yes. yes.
Your mom buried the original report.

409
00:33:59.914 --> 00:34:02.625
And she had some friends over
at the EPA and she gave them a call.

410
00:34:02.709 --> 00:34:05.127
And she paid them to doctor the numbers.

411
00:34:05.211 --> 00:34:06.922
Now why the fuck would she do that?

412
00:34:07.005 --> 00:34:08.297
For you.

413
00:34:08.382 --> 00:34:11.009
Because you were spiraling in LA.

414
00:34:11.092 --> 00:34:13.469
and Celine went to her
and promised to get you out

415
00:34:13.554 --> 00:34:18.141
and get you a big old fancy job
in New York City. Head of News.

416
00:34:18.224 --> 00:34:23.438
And Martha let you believe
that it was all you.

417
00:34:23.521 --> 00:34:25.273
Cory Ellison. boy genius.

418
00:34:25.356 --> 00:34:27.860
The brilliant son with the bright future.

419
00:34:30.027 --> 00:34:31.905
Stay away from my fucking wife.

420
00:34:46.628 --> 00:34:50.507
Even if I wanted to fight back.
she has all the leverage.

421
00:34:51.175 --> 00:34:54.385
I can't use the deepfake.
Bart won't go on the record.

422
00:34:55.094 --> 00:34:58.389
I mean. we can still. you know.
pass it off to another journalist.

423
00:34:59.391 --> 00:35:00.851
Laura Peterson.

424
00:35:00.934 --> 00:35:03.061
She called me to see
if she could do anything to help.

425
00:35:03.144 --> 00:35:05.856
I don't know about that. Given their
history. it might get a little muddy.

426
00:35:05.938 --> 00:35:07.190
Why don't you do it?

427
00:35:07.815 --> 00:35:10.277
You don't work for the company.
you haven't signed an NDA.

428
00:35:10.777 --> 00:35:13.447
Yeah. that sounds great. Martin.
Why don't you just throw me to the sharks

429
00:35:13.530 --> 00:35:14.907
- like a bucket of chum?
- Chip…

430
00:35:14.989 --> 00:35:16.199
Yeah.

431
00:35:16.867 --> 00:35:19.202
Look. Celine knows that
I've been working with Bradley.

432
00:35:19.286 --> 00:35:21.413
If I take a run at her.
she's gonna turn around and sue me.

433
00:35:21.496 --> 00:35:24.458
and then all of a sudden her attorneys
have access to all the information

434
00:35:24.541 --> 00:35:27.126
that Bradley sent over. including where
to find the whistleblowers.

435
00:35:27.210 --> 00:35:29.338
We can't do that.
They can't see our playbook.

436
00:35:29.420 --> 00:35:31.507
But we want to see their playbook.

437
00:35:32.215 --> 00:35:35.219
That's why you should sue her first.
beat her to the punch.

438
00:35:36.969 --> 00:35:39.056
A lawsuit will mean document production.

439
00:35:39.764 --> 00:35:42.893
Something embarrassing to them
might just slip through the cracks.

440
00:35:42.976 --> 00:35:44.436
You're looking for a smoking gun.

441
00:35:44.519 --> 00:35:45.603
Okay. so hold on.

442
00:35:46.271 --> 00:35:50.483
So you're saying that I should sue Celine
and UBN for wrongful termination.

443
00:35:50.567 --> 00:35:55.739
Yeah. Break your NDA. force their hand.
and see what comes out in the wash.

444
00:35:55.822 --> 00:35:58.699
If I do that. it's war.
I mean. it's full-on war.

445
00:35:58.784 --> 00:36:00.994
Yeah. she'll come for you.
There'll be casualties.

446
00:36:01.077 --> 00:36:02.996
Yes. of course
there are gonna be casualties.

447
00:36:03.079 --> 00:36:04.789
Look what happened to the lawyer
in Wolf River.

448
00:36:04.873 --> 00:36:06.541
They completely destroyed his life.

449
00:36:06.625 --> 00:36:08.126
- Chip. I…
- Alex. hold on a second.

450
00:36:08.210 --> 00:36:10.878
Listen to me. okay?
There are calculated risks.

451
00:36:10.963 --> 00:36:13.047
And then there are just suicide missions.

452
00:36:13.130 --> 00:36:15.342
The minute that you sue Celine.

453
00:36:15.425 --> 00:36:17.635
you put yourself
right in the fucking crosshairs.

454
00:36:17.719 --> 00:36:19.471
- And then once her family gets involved--
- So what?

455
00:36:19.554 --> 00:36:22.099
You're just saying that I don't say
a word. Just let her win. That's it.

456
00:36:22.181 --> 00:36:23.516
- Story over.
- Okay.

457
00:36:23.599 --> 00:36:25.393
- Well…
- Listen. Dad.

458
00:36:26.143 --> 00:36:27.646
You're the lawyer in the room.

459
00:36:28.230 --> 00:36:29.481
What would you do?

460
00:36:29.565 --> 00:36:33.235
If you sue her first.
then you start with the advantage.

461
00:36:33.318 --> 00:36:37.530
You catch her unawares.
She's got no idea you're coming for her.

462
00:37:01.262 --> 00:37:02.389
Yeah. who the fuck is this?

463
00:37:02.472 --> 00:37:04.432
Mr. Ellison.
it's Max Kimmel from The Vault.

464
00:37:04.516 --> 00:37:06.851
I'm calling about Alex Levy's resignation.

465
00:37:06.934 --> 00:37:08.686
No. I don't have any comment about that.

466
00:37:08.769 --> 00:37:11.898
I'm hearing a rumor
she's holding a press conference today.

467
00:37:11.981 --> 00:37:14.358
Some big revelation
about why she left UBN.

468
00:37:15.110 --> 00:37:16.445
You know anything about that?

469
00:37:17.653 --> 00:37:19.864
Mr. Ellison? Hello?

470
00:37:26.121 --> 00:37:28.081
- Hey.
- Gotta be kidding me.

471
00:37:28.164 --> 00:37:29.833
- Alex. just hold on.
- Honestly. Cory. just move.

472
00:37:29.916 --> 00:37:32.001
or I'm gonna take you outside
and throw you in front of a fucking bus.

473
00:37:32.085 --> 00:37:35.713
A press conference?
Are you out of your fucking mind?

474
00:37:35.797 --> 00:37:38.967
You don't take Celine Dumont
head on in public.

475
00:37:39.050 --> 00:37:42.179
Imagine… She's gonna turn over every rock.
everything that you've ever done.

476
00:37:42.262 --> 00:37:43.889
everything… everything that hurts.

477
00:37:43.972 --> 00:37:47.809
Everyone that you have ever fucked.
everyone you've ever fucked over.

478
00:37:47.893 --> 00:37:49.978
Bringing Bradley back after January 6th?

479
00:37:50.061 --> 00:37:53.023
That's coming out too.
And when it does. yeah. trust me.

480
00:37:53.106 --> 00:37:55.943
no one will believe a word that comes out
of your mouth ever again.

481
00:37:56.025 --> 00:37:58.152
You will be a punch line
on late-night television.

482
00:37:58.237 --> 00:37:59.695
and then you're gonna disappear.

483
00:38:00.197 --> 00:38:01.532
So be it.

484
00:38:01.614 --> 00:38:02.657
Oh. my…

485
00:38:04.534 --> 00:38:05.536
Alex. I swear to God.

486
00:38:05.619 --> 00:38:07.161
I'm trying to protect you. And Bradley.

487
00:38:07.246 --> 00:38:09.748
Is it? Is that why…
Is that why you're sleeping with Celine

488
00:38:09.831 --> 00:38:13.085
- while she's in a fucking prison cell?
- This is not how you do it.

489
00:38:13.168 --> 00:38:15.711
It actually is. This is how I do it.

490
00:38:15.795 --> 00:38:18.798
And you're right. I am gonna fuck up
my entire life but I don't give a shit.

491
00:38:18.882 --> 00:38:21.592
